<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm364243552"><term>designated leader</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm383796976">The person placed in the leadership position by forces outside the group.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm363216560"><term>emergent leader</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm383603200">The person who becomes a group’s leader by virtue of processes and dynamics internal to the group.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm374711664"><term>formal leader</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm368262608">That individual who is recognized by those outside the group as the official leader of the group.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm355223744"><term>informal leader</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm361882272">That individual whom members of the group acknowledge as their leader.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>

